verbose_text: The pyruvate-malate cycle proceeds with reductive metabolism of Pcx derived oxaloacetate into malate, which is exported into the cytosol, then acted upon by Me1 to produce the coupling factor nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide phosphate, reduced (NADPH) as pyruvate is regenerated (XREF_FIG).
evidence: Me1 to produce the coupling factor nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide phosphate
